rxOverflowHWFault.name: rxOverflowHWFault
rxOverflowHWFault.description: An RX buffer overflow has occurred in one of the LAN or link interfaces. The bound variable rndErrorDesc provides the interface number.

txOverflowHWFault.name: txOverflowHWFault
txOverflowHWFault.description: Interport queue overflow has occurred in one of the LAN or link interfaces. The bound variable rndErrorDesc provides the interface number.

routeTableOverflow.name: routeTableOverflow
routeTableOverflow.description: An overflow condition has occurred in the Routing Table. The Routing Table is used for IP routing algorithm (RIP).

resetRequired.name: resetRequired
resetRequired.description: This trap indicates that in order to perform the last SET request, a reset operation of the router/bridge is required. This occurs when the layer 2 routing algorithm is changed between SPF and Spanning Tree. The reset can be performed manually or using the variable rndAction.

endTftp.name: endTftp
endTftp.description: This trap indicates that in the device finished a TFTP transaction with the management station. variable rndErrorDesc and rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

abortTftp.name: abortTftp
abortTftp.description: This trap indicates that in the device aborted a TFTP session with the management station. Variable rndErrorDesc and rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

startTftp.name: startTftp
startTftp.description: Informational trap indicating that the device has intiated a TFTP session. rndErrorDesc will contain the file type in question

faultBackUp.name: faultBackUp
faultBackUp.description: Automantic switchover to backup link because of main link fault.

ipxRipTblOverflow.name: ipxRipTblOverflow
ipxRipTblOverflow.description: This trap indicates that in an OpenGate IPX RIP table overflow. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

ipxSapTblOverflow.name: ipxSapTblOverflow
ipxSapTblOverflow.description: This trap indicates that in an OpenGate IPX SAP table overflow. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

facsAccessVoilation.name: facsAccessVoilation
facsAccessVoilation.description: This trap indicates that message that fits FACS statenebt with operation blockAndReport was forward to the interface. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== info ) and interface Number.

autoConfigurationCompleted.name: autoConfigurationCompleted
autoConfigurationCompleted.description: This trap indicates that auto comfiguration completetd succssefully. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== info )

forwardingTabOverflow.name: forwardingTabOverflow
forwardingTabOverflow.description: This trap indicates that an overflow condition has occurred in the layer II Forward Table. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== warning )

framRelaySwitchConnectionUp.name: framRelaySwitchConnectionUp
framRelaySwitchConnectionUp.description: This trap indicates that a connection establish between the Frame relay Switch and the WanGate. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== warning )

framRelaySwitchConnectionDown.name: framRelaySwitchConnectionDown
framRelaySwitchConnectionDown.description: This trap indicates that a connection between the Frame Relay Switch and the WanGate failed. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== warning )

errorsDuringInit.name: errorsDuringInit
errorsDuringInit.description: This trap indicates that the an error occured during initialization The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== error )

rsSDclientsTableOverflow.name: rsSDclientsTableOverflow
rsSDclientsTableOverflow.description: This warning is generated when an overflow occurs in the clients table.

rsSDinactiveServer.name: rsSDinactiveServer
rsSDinactiveServer.description: This warning is generated when a server does not respond to the dispatchers polling and is thought to be inactive.

rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow.name: rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow
rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow.description: The Zero Hop Routing connections Table has been overflown.

rsIpZhrReqStaticConnNotAccepted.name: rsIpZhrReqStaticConnNotAccepted
rsIpZhrReqStaticConnNotAccepted.description: The requested static connection was not accepted because there is no available IP virtual address to allocate to it.

rsIpZhrVirtualIpAsSource.name: rsIpZhrVirtualIpAsSource
rsIpZhrVirtualIpAsSource.description: The virtual IP address appeared as a source IP. All the connections using it will be deleted and it will not be further allocated to new connections.

rsIpZhrNotAllocVirtualIp.name: rsIpZhrNotAllocVirtualIp
rsIpZhrNotAllocVirtualIp.description: The source IP address sent an ARP specifying a virtual IP which was not allocated for this source. This virtual IP will not be allocated to connections of this specific source IP.

rsSnmpSetRequestInSpecialCfgState.name: rsSnmpSetRequestInSpecialCfgState
rsSnmpSetRequestInSpecialCfgState.description: An incoming SNMP SET request was rejected because no such requests (except action requests) are accepted after start of new configuration reception or during sending the current configuration to an NMS.

rsPingCompletion.name: rsPingCompletion
rsPingCompletion.description: A rsPingCompleted trap is sent at the completion of a sequence of pings if such a trap was requested when the sequence was initiated. The trap severity is info. The trap text will specify the following information: rsPingCompletionStatus, rsPingSentPackets, rsPingReceivedPackets In addition to the above listed objects (which are always present), the message will also specify the following quantities: if any responses were received: rsPingMinReturnTime rsPingAvgReturnTime rsPingMaxReturnTime

pppSecurityViolation.name: pppSecurityViolation
pppSecurityViolation.description: This trap indicates that a PPP link got an unrecognized secret. The bound variables rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== warning ), interface Number. and pppSecurityIdentity

rsWSDRedundancySwitch.name: rsWSDRedundancySwitch
rsWSDRedundancySwitch.description: Whenever main server fails and backup takes over or server comes up after failure a trap of this type is issued.

rsDhcpAllocationFailure.name: rsDhcpAllocationFailure
rsDhcpAllocationFailure.description: DHCP failed to allocate an IP address to a requesting host because of memory shortage or inadequate configuration of available IP addresses.

rlPhysicalDescriptionChanged.name: rlPhysicalDescriptionChanged
rlPhysicalDescriptionChanged.description: Indicates that the physical decription of the device has changed

rldot1dStpPortStateForwarding.name: rldot1dStpPortStateForwarding
rldot1dStpPortStateForwarding.description: The trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

rldot1dStpPortStateNotForwarding.name: rldot1dStpPortStateNotForwarding
rldot1dStpPortStateNotForwarding.description: The trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state.

rlPolicyDropPacketTrap.name: rlPolicyDropPacketTrap
rlPolicyDropPacketTrap.description: Indicates that the packet drop due to the policy

rlPolicyForwardPacketTrap.name: rlPolicyForwardPacketTrap
rlPolicyForwardPacketTrap.description: Indicates that the packet has forward based on policy

rlIgmpV1MsgReceived.name: rlIgmpV1MsgReceived
rlIgmpV1MsgReceived.description: An IGMP Message of v1 received on ifIndex.

rlVrrpEntriesDeleted.name: rlVrrpEntriesDeleted
rlVrrpEntriesDeleted.description: One or more VRRP entries deleted due to IP interface deletion or transition.

rlTrunkPortAddedTrap.name: rlTrunkPortAddedTrap
rlTrunkPortAddedTrap.description: Informational trap indicating that a port is added to a trunk

rlTrunkPortRemovedTrap.name: rlTrunkPortRemovedTrap
rlTrunkPortRemovedTrap.description: This warning is generated when a port removed from a trunk.

rlTrunkPortNotCapableTrap.name: rlTrunkPortNotCapableTrap
rlTrunkPortNotCapableTrap.description: Informational trap indicating that a port can not be added to a trunk because of device limitations or diffrent swIfType.

rlLockPortTrap.name: rlLockPortTrap
rlLockPortTrap.description: Informational trap indicating that a locked port receive a frame with new source Mac Address.

vlanDynamicToStatic.name: vlanDynamicToStatic
vlanDynamicToStatic.description: vlan status was changed from dynamic to static

vlanStaticToDynamic.name: vlanStaticToDynamic
vlanStaticToDynamic.description: vlan status was changed from static to dynamic

dstrSysLog.name: dstrSysLog
dstrSysLog.description: Master receive trap from slave , and forward it as trap

rlEnvMonFanStateChange.name: rlEnvMonFanStateChange
rlEnvMonFanStateChange.description: Trap indicating the fan state. rndErrorSeverity will be: 0 for fan state nomal, notPresent 1 for fan state warning, notFunctioning 2 for fan state critical 3 for fan state fatal The error text will specify the fan index, fan description and the exact fan state

rlEnvMonPowerSupplyStateChange.name: rlEnvMonPowerSupplyStateChange
rlEnvMonPowerSupplyStateChange.description: Trap indicating the power supply state. rndErrorSeverity will be: 0 for power supply state nomal, notPresent 1 for power supply state warning, notFunctioning 2 for power supply state critical 3 for power supply state fatal The error text will specify the power supply index, power supply description and the exact power supply state

rlStackStateChange.name: rlStackStateChange
rlStackStateChange.description: Trap indicating the stack connection state 0 for stack state connected, 1 for stack state disconnected

rlEnvMonTemperatureRisingAlarm.name: rlEnvMonTemperatureRisingAlarm
rlEnvMonTemperatureRisingAlarm.description: Trap indicating that the temperature in the device has exceeded the device specific safe temperature threshold.

rlBrgMacAddFailedTrap.name: rlBrgMacAddFailedTrap
rlBrgMacAddFailedTrap.description: Informational trap indicating that adding dynamic mac/s failed due to full hash chain.

rldot1xPortStatusAuthorizedTrap.name: rldot1xPortStatusAuthorizedTrap
rldot1xPortStatusAuthorizedTrap.description: Informational trap indicating that port 802.1x status is authorized.

rldot1xPortStatusUnauthorizedTrap.name: rldot1xPortStatusUnauthorizedTrap
rldot1xPortStatusUnauthorizedTrap.description: Warning trap is indicating that port 802.1x status is unAuthorized.

swIfTablePortLock.name: swIfTablePortLock
swIfTablePortLock.description: Warning trap is indicating port lock hase began.

swIfTablePortUnLock.name: swIfTablePortUnLock
swIfTablePortUnLock.description: Warning trap is indicating port lock has ended.

rlAAAUserLocked.name: rlAAAUserLocked
rlAAAUserLocked.description: Warning trap indicating that the user was locked after number of consecutives unsuccessful login attempts.

bpduGuardPortSuspended.name: bpduGuardPortSuspended
bpduGuardPortSuspended.description: Warning trap indicating - Port was suspended because there was BPDU Guard violation.

rldot1xSupplicantMacAuthorizedTrap.name: rldot1xSupplicantMacAuthorizedTrap
rldot1xSupplicantMacAuthorizedTrap.description: Informational trap indicating that MAC authentication supplicant is authenticated and is allowed to access the network.

rldot1xSupplicantMacUnauthorizedTrap.name: rldot1xSupplicantMacUnauthorizedTrap
rldot1xSupplicantMacUnauthorizedTrap.description: Warning trap is indicating that Radius server rejects MAC authentication supplicant.

stpLoopbackDetection.name: stpLoopbackDetection
stpLoopbackDetection.description: Warning trap indicating - A loopback was detected on port.

stpLoopbackDetectionResolved.name: stpLoopbackDetectionResolved
stpLoopbackDetectionResolved.description: Warning trap indicating - A loopback detection resolved on port.

loopbackDetectionPortSuspended.name: loopbackDetectionPortSuspended
loopbackDetectionPortSuspended.description: Warning trap indicating - A port has been suspended by Loopback Detection.

rlSwStormControlSuspend.name: rlSwStormControlSuspend
rlSwStormControlSuspend.description: Warning trap indicating - Port was suspended because there was storm violation.
